# Audio pipeline architecture

Calliop processes voice dictation through a linear pipeline orchestrated in `pipeline/`.

## Flow

```
Hotkey (toggle ON / push-to-talk hold)
  -> AudioCapture (PCM 16 kHz mono, streaming chunks)
  -> VadSegmenter (Silero VAD, filters silence)
  -> WhisperEngine (persistent context, segment transcription)
  -> partial-transcript events -> Overlay
Hotkey OFF / release (toggle or PTT)
  -> flush VAD tail + concat segments
  -> apply_corrections (dictionary misspelling rules, manual words only)
  -> get_active_window + resolve_tone (app_context/, SQLite rules cache)
  -> optional LlamaEngine cleanup (sidecar, tone-aware system prompt, 4s wait, KV-cached system prefix, fallback post-processed)
  -> apply_snippets (deterministic trigger expansion, verbatim + auto-edit)
  -> TextInjector (inject/)
  -> optional CorrectionWatcher (observe/, Windows UIA, if auto_learn)
  -> latency-metrics event (sttMs, llmMs, injectMs, totalMs)
  -> SQLite dictations table + FTS5 index (store/history.rs, if text non-empty)
  -> history-updated event
```

## Module responsibilities

| Module | Path | Role |
|-----|---|---|
| hotkey | `hotkey/` | Global shortcut configurable (default Alt+Space hybrid toggle/PTT) |
| inference | `inference/` | Backend selection: CPU default, optional Vulkan via cargo feature `gpu` |
| audio | `audio/` | Micro capture via cpal, VAD segmentation |
| stt | `stt/` | Local transcription (whisper.cpp / whisper-rs) |
| llm | `llm/` | Post-processing auto-edits via `calliop-llm-worker` sidecar (llama.cpp) |
| inject | `inject/` | Paste/type into foreground app (enigo + clipboard fallback) |
| store | `store/` | SQLite: config (`auto_edit`, `auto_learn`, `stt_language`), dictionary, snippets, `app_context_rules`, history |
| observe | `observe/` | Post-injection UIA watcher: detect user corrections in target app (Windows) |
| app_context | `app_context/` | Foreground window detection (Win32), tone profile resolution per app |
| pipeline | `pipeline/` | Orchestration, state machine, IPC bridge to frontend |

## LLM sidecar (Phase 3a)

- Main binary links **whisper-rs only** — no `llama-cpp-2` in-process (ggml symbol conflict).
- Sidecar binary: `calliop-llm-worker` (workspace crate `crates/calliop-llm-worker`), spawned on `ensure_llm_model`.
- Models: **Qwen3 0.6B** or **Qwen3 1.7B** Instruct Q4_K_M GGUF (`llm_model` in SQLite), lazy download when `auto_edit` is enabled.
- Sidecar accepts `--ngl` (GPU layers); `0` when `inference_backend=cpu`.
- Verbatim mode: `auto_edit = false` in SQLite — inject raw Whisper transcript.
- Dev: `pnpm tauri:dev` builds the sidecar via `scripts/dev.ps1`.

## IPC (Tauri commands)

- Frontend (React) handles overlay, settings, onboarding — no heavy ML in the webview.
- Rust core exposes commands for start/stop dictation, settings read/write, history queries.
- Commands: `get_settings`, `set_settings`, `get_models_status`, `delete_model`, `get_inference_info`, `set_hotkey`, `is_onboarding_done`, `set_onboarding_done`, `start_mic_probe`, `stop_mic_probe`, `get_stt_language`, `cycle_dictation_language`, `ensure_model`, `ensure_llm_model`, `list_dictionary_words`, `add_dictionary_word(word, misspelling?)`, `remove_dictionary_word`, `learn_from_correction`, `list_snippets`, `add_snippet`, `remove_snippet`, `import_snippets`, `export_snippets`, `get_active_window`, `list_app_context_rules`, `add_app_context_rule`, `remove_app_context_rule`, `list_dictations`, `search_dictations`, `copy_dictation`, `reinject_dictation`, `get_insights`, `is_autostart_enabled`, `set_autostart_enabled`
- Events: `pipeline-state`, `partial-transcript`, `audio-level` (`level` + `bands[14]`), `latency-metrics`, `stt-language-changed`, `model-download-progress`, `model-ready`, `llm-model-download-progress`, `llm-ready`, `dictionary-updated`, `snippets-updated`, `app-context-updated`, `history-updated`
- Dictionary words and snippet triggers are cached as a Whisper `initial_prompt` string (`Arc<RwLock<Option<Arc<str>>>>` in pipeline); refreshed on CRUD and on startup.
- Manual dictionary entries may store an optional `misspelling`; active rules are cached in `correction_rules` (`Arc<RwLock<Vec<CorrectionRule>>>`) and applied via `pipeline/corrections.rs` after STT, before snippets/LLM.
- Snippet triggers are expanded deterministically in `pipeline/snippets.rs` after LLM cleanup (or on raw transcript in verbatim mode), before injection.
- `auto_learn` (default on): after inject, `observe/` polls the focused control via UIA for ~60s; stabilized corrections call `apply_learned_correction` (same path as in-app `learn_from_correction`).

## Inference backend (Phase 4)

- SQLite `inference_backend`: `auto` (default) or `cpu`.
- Cargo feature `gpu` enables Vulkan for whisper-rs + llama-cpp-2 sidecar (Windows dev/build via `scripts/tauri-cli.mjs`).
- `auto` uses GPU layers when compiled with `gpu`; ggml falls back to CPU if no device.
- STT: `WhisperEngine::new_with_gpu(path, use_gpu)`; LLM: sidecar `--ngl 99` or `--ngl 0`.
- Whisper models: `small` / `distil-fr-dec16` (`whisper_model` in SQLite; legacy `medium` maps to distil); switch reloads engine via `set_settings`.

## Phase scope

- Phase 1: hotkey -> audio -> stt -> inject (no LLM, no VAD)
- Phase 2: Silero VAD, streaming by segments, overlay, tray menu, autostart, latency debug
- STT: **whisper-rs 0.16**, persistent `WhisperEngine`, modèle `ggml-small.bin`, langue `fr`
- Audio capture runs on a dedicated thread (`cpal` streams are !Send)
- Phase 3a: LLM auto-edits via sidecar, SQLite `auto_edit` toggle
- Phase 3d: per-app tone profiles (`casual` / `formal` / `technical`) via `app_context_rules` + Win32 foreground detection; tone passed to LLM sidecar only when `auto_edit` is on
- Phase 3e: STT language `fr` / `en` / `auto` in SQLite (`stt_language`); Whisper `set_detect_language` for auto; session override per dictation; overlay badge cycles language mid-recording via `cycle_dictation_language`
- Phase 3f–3g: `dictations` + `dictations_fts` (FTS5) in SQLite; persist after inject with latencies, word count, audio duration, active window exe/title; `get_insights` aggregates WPM (vs 40 WPM typing baseline), daily/total words, learned corrections, per-app usage
- Phase 3.5 perf: streaming capture accumulates 16 kHz PCM (no raw-buffer clone/resample on stop); bounded `sync_channel(64)` with non-blocking `try_send`; reusable I16/U16 convert scratch; persistent `WhisperState` across segments; LLM sidecar reuses one `LlamaContext` with `clear_kv_cache` between cleanups; `WhisperPromptCache` incremental dictionary prompt updates (`list_words_for_prompt` by recency); `DictionaryNotifier` debounced OS toast + `dictionary-updated` payload `{ added, removed, source }`; autostart `--minimized` defers Whisper/LLM load until first hotkey (`ensure_model_then_start`); correction watcher bumps `observer_generation` per injection; UIA `thread_local` reuse on watcher thread
- Phase 3.5 adaptive perf: `system/capabilities` (Win32 RAM + CPU cores); `system/profile` resolves `RuntimePerfConfig` (tier eco/balanced/performance, VAD chunk 256–1024, STT threads, preload flags); SQLite `whisper_model`/`llm_model` value `auto` (default) with manual override; `low_power_mode` (LLM lazy on first dictation stop, Whisper unload after 10 min idle + `model-unready` event); `adaptive_perf` toggles chunk/threads; smart boot preload via `preload_whisper`/`preload_llm` from resolved config; IPC `get_inference_info` exposes tier, RAM, effective models, VAD chunk
- Phase 4: Settings UI (Général / Modèles / Raccourcis / Avancé); onboarding first-launch (`onboarding_done`); hotkey persisted in SQLite + re-registered via `set_hotkey`; model registry in `stt/model.rs` + `llm/model.rs`
